<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Echo world!</title>
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/css/style.css' />
  </head>
  <body>
  	<div id="container">
      <div class="outer">
        <div class="middle">
          <h1>{{msg}}</h1>
          <div class="desc">
            <p>
              Just change the string in the url, and it will magically be echoed back here.
            </p>
            <p>
              This little echo web service was made using
              <a href="http://nodejs.org/">nodeJS</a>,
              <a href="http://expressjs.com/">express</a>,
              <a href="http://twitter.github.io/hogan.js/">hogan</a>,
              <a href="http://lesscss.org/">less</a> 
              and 
              <a href="http://gruntjs.com/">grunt</a>.
              <br/>
              Need to check out the code? Grab it from 
              <a href="http://github.com/pirhanas/nodeecho">here</a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <script type="text/javascript" src="/js/script.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>